/**
 * LogoAsset.gs
 * The default WCM logo, embedded directly as code instead of read from Drive at runtime.
 *
 * Earlier approaches all depended on Drive access at render time and each broke a different way:
 * pasting the full-size logo's base64 into Dashboard.html got silently truncated by hand; asking
 * Drive for an auto-generated thumbnail sometimes returned an HTML error page instead of image
 * bytes; and reading a small file directly by ID still requires the Apps Script project's
 * execution identity to have access to that specific Drive file, which is not guaranteed if it
 * was uploaded from a different Google account than the one the script runs as.
 *
 * Embedding the (already small — ~170px tall, ~17KB) PNG as a string constant removes all of
 * that: nothing is fetched at runtime, so there is no file ID, no permissions, and no network
 * call that can fail. This is the logo shown until someone uploads a different one via the
 * dashboard's own "Change logo" control (see DashboardServer.gs/uploadLogo_), which is now the
 * normal way to change it — no code edit needed. Editing the string below is only for changing
 * what the *default* falls back to (e.g. after a "Reset to default" click) if you ever want that
 * to be a different image; a plain code edit still works exactly as before if you prefer it.
 */
const WCM_LOGO_BASE64 = '';
